                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00 Tsinan/35: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-05-09T18:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 9, 1928—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>153. Shanghai’s telegram of May 5, noon, repeating Price’s telegram of May 4, 11
                    a.m.</p>
                <p>With reference to third paragraph of Price’s telegram Department desires that you
                    inform Price that if and as soon as good offices asked by authorities on both
                    sides, he is authorized, with or without his consular colleagues, to mediate to
                    terminate fighting. Instruct him to telegraph momentarily any developments in
                    this connection.</p>
                <p>Department also desires your own views as to possibility of mediation.</p>
                <p>Repeat to Tokyo.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
